message: To succeed, extract solid ingredients with the vial to create 30-value liquids. For initial liquid ingredients (not extracted), use the filter to also create 30-value liquids. Combining two 30-value liquids (either two mundane, two magical, or one of each) usually yields a 60-value item. The highest score (100) comes from combining an *extracted mundane* liquid with a *filtered magical* liquid. message: Focus on using the vial on solid ingredients first. Combining a magical solid's extract with a mundane solid's extract consistently yields a score of 100. For example, 'vial' + 'unicorn horn' (magical solid) then 'vial' + 'mushroom' (mundane solid), then combine the two resulting extracts. Filters are generally less useful for initial extracts, often reducing their value, but can convert gases into liquids or sometimes improve complex, low-value mixtures.
